##Teachers and schools in Shanghai have fought tooth and nail to give new books to children

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Han Xiaorong is a reporter for the paper

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Parents at Bidor home No. 1 Primary School in Shanghai Don face masks and queue up more than a metre apart. All pictures were provided by the respondents

Teachers and parents in Shanghai cooperate well with each other when the textbooks are safely delivered to their children.

At Bidor home No. 1 Primary School in Shanghai, all teachers who handed out textbooks were kept at a distance of more than one meter, and parents in each class wore masks at the same distance of one meter each.

Affected by the outbreak, more than 1.4 million primary and secondary school students in Shanghai have started online education since March 2. The Shanghai Municipal Education Commission has requested that on the basis of distributing electronic teaching materials, schools adhere to the "disinfection prevention and control, voluntary appointment, decentralized collection, to ensure safety" principle, the paper-based teaching materials have been launched in succession to ensure that students on March 2 before the launch of online learning, a set of paper-based teaching materials or electronic teaching materials.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Teachers distribute teaching materials

Parents line up for textbooks one meter apart

According to the requirements of the Shanghai Municipal Education Commission and the Baoshan District Education Bureau, the school, in consultation with parents, asked the parents of Bidor No. 1 Primary School in Bidor, Shanghai, a flexible paper-based teaching material distribution programme has been developed. The school should make the appointment registration well in advance, and arrange the time, place and mode of collection reasonably. The paper-based teaching materials can be collected at school and sent by express mail.

According to the data from the pre-school consultation form, most parents come to the school voluntarily to collect teaching materials. To that end, Bidor spent two or three days in small batches, disinfecting and repackaging textbooks for the entire student body.

The school attaches great importance to the health prevention and control measures in the distribution of teaching materials. Teachers First Take Body temperature at the school gate, fill in registration forms, then put on gloves and masks, and carry out book-sharing operations in full force.

From the book to the inventory, and then to the final packing, all teachers to maintain a distance of more than one meter, to ensure the distribution of the relative independence, to avoid cross-links. In addition, Bidor also arranged for a small logistics staff to carry out the final disinfection of teaching materials.

The school has also designed in advance a road map and process plan for parents to receive teaching materials. From 8:00 am to 4:00 pm, each class set aside an hour to distribute teaching materials, each class parents consciously put on masks, more than one meter between each other to queue, teaching materials distribution and collection work carried out in an orderly manner.

Similarly, Xingzhi middle school also adopts the principle of Grade Division, Class Division, Time Division and non-contact, and arranges the teaching staff to finish the distribution of the paper-based teaching materials and do a good job in cleaning and disinfecting the teaching materials and venues.

At the material collection site, the school pasted a yellow warning strip on the ground at 1-meter intervals and placed a conspicuous diagram on the blackboard at the entrance to inform the parents of the material collection process. Under the guidance of the school, each parent will queue up in an orderly manner one meter apart. After entering the Registration Office, the head teacher will check the student ID card and bring the teaching materials. In addition, the school also has an inventory of teaching materials, a table for each person, affixed with a list of teaching materials and placed for the use of parents.

At shensong Middle School in Minhang district, teachers are sorting and packing so fast that people are amazed. A magical "soul sorter" video that has been circulating on the Internet has made teachers famous again on the Internet. The teachers of Shensong Middle School constantly standardize the operation process, gradually improving work efficiency, soon completed two school districts of nearly 3000 students sorting and packing of textbooks. After such "devil training, " the teachers joked, they had mastered the skills of a sorter.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every parent in Xingzhi middle school will queue up for teaching materials one meter apart.

Delivered materials to 2,294 students

"Shanghai Kangcheng" is the largest community in Shanghai. Kangcheng school is located in this community. The whole school has nearly 3000 students.

Due to the concentration of students, the school, after consultation with the Communist Party Committee of the Kangcheng Community, the Industry Committee and the School Home Committee, finally decided to overcome the difficulties and change the way that parents come to the school to collect the textbooks to the school, both the maximum conservation of social resources, but also to avoid the accumulation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Teachers and volunteers at the Cannes school are skilled at packing and delivering textbooks to their homes.

When the plan was decided, the school recruited volunteers and acted quickly. All the administrative, party members, support staff, parents and volunteers, as well as volunteers from the "two committees and one center" of Lohas Park, Lohas Park residential area, have joined forces, in one and a half days, we delivered textbooks to 2,294 students living in Kangcheng district. After the parents receive the teaching material, even laments the school to deliver the teaching material efficiently, is also deeply moved by the volunteers'hard work to distribute.

According to a person in charge of the Minhang district education bureau, starting from February 19,149 schools in the district, with a total of 163293 primary and middle school students, have started distributing teaching materials to ensure that students in both Shanghai and other provinces will be able to attend school by February 28, a set of paper or electronic textbooks is available to all.
